<br>
<br>
<DIV class="poemtitle">The New House</DIV><br>
  <div align="center"><img src="images/newhouse.jpg"><br>
  <a class="artistline" href="javascript:goauthor('jones');">art by Pat Jones</a></div>
<br>
<TABLE><TR><TD>
<br>
<br>
Enough! <br />
Unstick yourself from that populous bed. <br />
Tour the new listing with me. <br />
<br />
Quite an open floor plan, no?&#8212;<br />
evidence of a great teardown. <br />
Those ridges in the hardwood <br />
mark the footprints of the old viewing rooms.<br> 
Right where you’re standing, <br />
people knelt and wept, <br />
painted corpses were laid out in satin. <br />
<br />
These floor windows are the latest model. <br />
Open them with this remote <br />
and with this butane matchstick, <br />
light the grand fire pit. <br />
<br />
A prime selling point, that. <br />
An ideal place to entertain, <br />
to share smokes, <br />
char dogs on sticks, <br />
sway in unison to the rhythm of falling embers. <br />
<br />
Why so jumpy? <br />
Haven’t you known all along <br />
that you were pre-approved? <br />
Simple, simple: <br />
no waiting, no escrow, <br />
no convoluted clauses to puzzle over. <br />
The place is as furnished as it’s going to be. <br />
Welcome, dear, to your new home.<br />
<br />
<br /><br>

<a class="byline" href="javascript:goauthor('benedict')">by Kate Bernadette Benedict</a><br><br><br>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
</div>
		
